  "prompt": "Cost for 1kg of A is 260 USD and 1kg of B is 380. AB is made by mixing A and B. If 1kg of AB costs 300, what was the ratio that A and B has mixed?",
  "response": "To determine the ratio in which substances A and B are mixed to form 1 kg of AB, let's set up the problem with the given information:\n\n- **Cost of A**: \\$260 per kg\n- **Cost of B**: \\$380 per kg\n- **Total cost of AB**: \\$300 per kg\n- **Total mass of AB**: 1 kg\n\nLet's denote:\n- \\( x \\) = mass of A in the mixture (in kg)\n- \\( y \\) = mass of B in the mixture (in kg)\n\nWe have two equations based on the mass and cost:\n\n1. **Mass Equation:**\n   \\[\n   x + y = 1\n   \\]\n\n2. **Cost Equation:**\n   \\[\n   260x + 380y = 300\n   \\]\n\n**Step-by-Step Solution:**\n\n1. **Express \\( y \\) in terms of \\( x \\):**\n   \\[\n   y = 1 - x\n   \\]\n\n2. **Substitute \\( y \\) into the cost equation:**\n   \\[\n   260x + 380(1 - x) = 300\n   \\]\n   \\[\n   260x + 380 - 380x = 300\n   \\]\n   \\[\n   -120x + 380 = 300\n   \\]\n   \\[\n   -120x = -80\n   \\]\n   \\[\n   x = \\frac{80}{120} = \\frac{2}{3} \\, \\text{kg}\n   \\]\n\n3. **Find \\( y \\):**\n   \\[\n   y = 1 - \\frac{2}{3} = \\frac{1}{3} \\, \\text{kg}\n   \\]\n\n4. **Determine the ratio of A to B:**\n   \\[\n   \\text{Ratio of A to B} = \\frac{x}{y} = \\frac{\\frac{2}{3}}{\\frac{1}{3}} = 2:1\n   \\]\n\n**Conclusion:**\n\nSubstance A and B are mixed in a **2:1 ratio** respectively to form 1 kg of AB.\n\n**Answer:** The substances A and B are mixed in a\u202f2 to\u00a01 ratio.",
